                                                   Yuvraj recovery

      A CORRESPONDENT
           
	Melbourne: Yuvraj Singhs recovery has been dramatic and he will be fit in time for the second one-dayer in Brisbane on Tuesday. 
    
	The lefthander visited an orthopaedic on Thursday who was more than happy with his recovery. India play Sri Lanka in the second match after opening the tri-series against Australia on Sunday. 
    
	Yuvraj had injured himself during practice in Perth. 
                                                   
